Sudanese President Bashir Calls for Industry Tax Cuts, SUNA Says

-- B y   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 
2011-08-16T08:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/sudanese-president-bashir-calls-for-industry-tax-cuts-suna-says.html
Sudanese President Umar al-Bashir
proposed lowering or abolishing taxes and fees for industrial
investors and providing them with land without charge, the
state-run SUNA news agency  reported  yesterday.  Al-Bashir also called on the ministries of oil and
electricity to conduct studies on cutting energy prices for
industry, SUNA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maram Mazen in Khartoum at 
 mmazen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 